"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-oliver-morgan-paris-olympics-backstroke-record-british-swimming-championships-b1149341.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport  Oliver Morganset a new British men's 100metre backstroke record to qualify for theParis Olympicsas he retained his title at theBritish Swimming Championshipsin London.  The 20-year-old University of Birmingham swimmer, also defending his British 50m and 200m backstroke titles at the London Aquatics Centre, clocked 52.70 seconds to break the previous record set by Liam Tancock 15 years ago.  Morgan finished well inside the Olympic qualifying time to take gold ahead of second-placed Jonathon Marshall and Luke Greenbank.  \\\"If you asked me two years ago if I would be in this position I'd have said there is no way,\\\" Morgan, who did not start competing at national level until he was 16, said of his rapid rise afterwards.  \\\"I can not put it into words. It proves you do not have to be there as a youngster. I did what I enjoyed when I was young. I played football and mountain biked.\\\"  Amelie Blocksidge retained her women's 1500m freestyle title at the age of 14.  Blocksidge, 15 next week, finished three seconds outside her personal best in 16.13:39 and well adrift of the Olympic qualification time, ahead of Loughborough University pair Fleur Lewis and Lucie Hanquet.  Brahim Diaz penalty theory debunked after Morocco AFCON final heartbreak  Tottenham vs Borussia Dortmund: Prediction, kick-off time, team news, odds, h2h  Spurs face new crisis as Solanke among up to 14 stars out for Dortmund  Reset your wellbeing for the year ahead  Scotland's Kara Hanlon swam a new lifetime's best of 2:24.59 after a strong finish to win the women's 200m breaststroke crown ahead of Somerset's Lily Booker.  Hanlon's fellow Scot Kathleen Dawson put her injury woes behind her by winning the 100m backstroke title in an Olympic qualifying time to seal her place for Paris.  Joshua Gammon won gold in the men's 200m butterfly in a new personal best of 1.56:95, just outside the Olympic qualifying time, with the University of Aberdeen's Thomas Beeley taking silver and Henry Gray finishing third.  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"